# Delivery Pipeline Framework

## Pipeline Paths

| Path | Risk | Stages |
|---|---|---|
| S | 1–2 | `ba → tech-lead → dev → reviewer (inline QA)` |
| M | 3 | `ba → sa → [designer?] → tech-lead → dev → qa → reviewer` |
| L | 4–5 | `ba → sa → [security-design?] → tech-lead → dev → [devops?] → qa → [security-review?] → reviewer` |

`ba` handles both BA + domain modeling (no separate `domain-analyst` stage).
`[]` = conditional stage. Stage gates, verdicts → AGENTS.md.

---

## Feature Location Convention (CD-22 locked tree)

| Pipeline type | Path | Map (atomic) |
|---|---|---|
| Feature (all repo types) | `docs/modules/M-NNN-{slug}/features/F-NNN-{slug}/` | `docs/intel/feature-map.yaml` |
| Module | `docs/modules/M-NNN-{slug}/` | `docs/intel/module-map.yaml` |
| Hotfix | `docs/hotfixes/H-NNN-{slug}/` | `docs/intel/feature-map.yaml` (hotfix entry) |
| Cross-cutting feature (CD-24) | Same nested path under primary owner module; secondary owners in `feature-catalog.features[].consumed_by_modules[]` |

**Path resolution**: `Bash("ai-kit sdlc resolve --kind {feature|module|hotfix} --id {ID}")` — atomic, ai-kit Node-native, single source of truth. ai-kit CLI unavailable → **BLOCK pipeline** per ADR-005 D3 (no Glob fallback).

**Producers** (call ai-kit CLI): `ai-kit sdlc scaffold feature` / `scaffold module` / `scaffold hotfix` (atomic update of state file + intel maps + catalogs).
**Consumers** (call ai-kit CLI): `ai-kit sdlc resolve` for lookup, `ai-kit sdlc verify --scopes structure` for integrity.

