## Changes-Requested Re-entry

| Reviewer finding | Re-entry stage |
|---|---|
| Code defects only | `dev` (skip ba/sa/tech-lead) |
| Scope drift / missing AC | `ba` → fast-track to dev |
| Architecture flaw | `sa` → `tech-lead` → `dev` |
| Security finding | `dev` with security guidance |

Max 2 rework cycles before escalating to user.

---

## Key Constraints

- Max 8 dev agents per wave; no overlapping ownership in same wave
- Max 2 refinement loops per agent pair before escalating
- Artifact language: English. Skills may override for user-facing responses.
- `_state.md` schema: validated via `Bash("ai-kit sdlc verify --scopes schemas")` (note: schema-level JSON validation deferred during ADR-005 transition; structure / cross_references / id_uniqueness scopes fully ported. Use Python `etc-platform verify --scopes schemas` for full schema validation until B-031 cutoff). Canonical schemas under `team-ai-config/bin/lib/sdlc/` (Node-native templates) and Python `etc-platform/src/etc_platform/assets/schemas/intel/_state.md.schema.json` (per CD-23 oneOf discriminator on `pipeline-type: sdlc | hotfix`). `_feature.md` schema: same paths.

---

## Session Context Resolution (ADR-005 D3 compliant)

```
1. Bash("ai-kit sdlc resolve --kind {feature|module|hotfix} --id {ID}") → atomic
2. ai-kit CLI unavailable → BLOCK pipeline per ADR-005 D3:
   "Install/update ai-kit CLI: ai-kit update. Verify via ai-kit doctor."
3. Multiple active pipelines → ask user which one (NEVER write to shared global state).
4. Git branch context (informational only, not authoritative): git branch --show-current
```

**No Glob fallback.** Pre-CD-8 v3 fallback (`glob docs/features/**/_state.md`) is FORBIDDEN — agents must BLOCK instead of mutating workspace at non-canonical paths.

